# WNUT-2016-derived evaluation sets: these contain rehydrated tweet text, and
# Twitter/X terms allow redistributing tweet IDs only, not content. Regenerate
# locally from your licensed WNUT copy with eval/adapters/wnut2016_to_geolens.py.
eval/wnut2016_*.csv
# ...except the tweet-ID + label manifest, which is shareable and committed for reproducibility.
!eval/wnut2016_id_manifest.csv
# (eval/results/*.json hold aggregate metrics + run manifest only, no tweet text, so they are committed.)
